<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Is the NES the &quot;glitchiest&quot; system?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10814&amp;p=124172#p124172"><![CDATA[
One inefficiency I've read about is that some engines overtessellate what doesn't need to be tessellated. Another is using primitives other than triangle/quad strips; I've read that GPUs aren't so efficient at handling fans and isolated triangles. Yet another is overly complex shaders.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Jan 19, 2014 2:46 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
